द्रामिडाचार्य
DramidAchArya, shrIvatsAnka-mishra etc. were (pre shankara likely) vedAntins who fed into later rAmAnuja's vishiShTAdvaita, but still different. Eg. Yamunacharya and Ramanuja explicitly disagree over some view of Dramidacharya. 

एकान्ती
He is called Ekantin who prays to Bhagavan for moksha as well as for the good things of this life but worships no other deity. 

परमैकान्ती
He is a Paramaikantin who, while praying only to Bhagavan, does not pray for anything other than bhakti and jnāna and their fruit moksha.

