स्वशेषभूत
literally, “his remnant” or, in the sense operative in the Mīmāṃsāsūtras, “belonging entirely to him”; see Mīmāṃsāsūtras 3.3.1–7.

श्रीवत्स
The śrīvatsa is a curl of hair on the chest of Viṣṇu—and of Kr̥ṣṇa—in a cruciform design.

पाञ्चजन्य
conch which myth takes to be the demon Pāñcajana who lives in the depths of the ocean in the form of a shell which Kr̥ṣṇa seized.

कौमोदकी
the mace which Agni gave to Kr̥ṣṇa before his battle with Indra.

सर्वाधिकारी
One who has adhikAra to give dIkSha of mantra-s of devata-s of all sects and sthApAnA of their images.


